Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @shallot{1} (all for 4 servings). Peel and
mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add
shallot; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add @peas{4%oz} and cook until lightly charred, stirring
occasionally, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @bavette steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least
~{3%minutes}. Wash out pan.

== Lemony Panko ==

While steak cooks, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a small pan over medium
heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and half the garlic; cook, stirring,
until panko is golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in lemon zest to taste. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to a plate.

== Dijon Steak Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add
remaining garlic and @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste; cook, stirring occasionally,
until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @peach jam{1}, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp},
and @water{1/4%cup}; cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @crème fraîche{2%tbsp} and a squeeze of lemon
juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== Arugula Salad ==

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together remaining mustard, a drizzle of olive oil,
a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Add @arugula lettuce{2%oz} and charred veggies to bowl; toss to coat. Taste
and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Halve @burrata{4%oz} into rounds; season
cut sides with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between plates and arrange steak alongside. Top salad with burrata
and sprinkle with as much lemony panko as you like. Drizzle steak sauce over
steak. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Looking for a steak dinner with a bit more style? Meet burrata and arugula—a
> deluxe duo that's simplest way to turn your dinner divine. This extra-rich
> mozzarella is served over a mix of arugula, charred peas, and a bright
> Dijon dressing, then sprinkled with a lemony toasted panko. For the main
> event, bavette steak is seared and drizzled with a tangy steak sauce,
> sweetened with peach jam. That's one snazzy steak 'n' salad!